{
  "bookId": "laozi-wangbi-wiki",
  "num": 23,
  "title": "第二十三章",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "希言自然。"
    },
    {
      "text": "故飄風不終朝，驟雨不終日。孰為此者？天地。天地尚不能久，而況於人乎？"
    },
    {
      "text": "故從事於道者，道者同於道，"
    },
    {
      "text": "德者同於德，"
    },
    {
      "text": "失者同於失。"
    },
    {
      "text": "同於道者，道亦樂得之；同於德者，德亦樂得之；同於失者，失亦樂得之。"
    },
    {
      "text": "信不足焉，有不信焉。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聽之不聞名曰希，下章言，道之出言淡兮其無味也，視之不足見，聽之不足聞，然則無味不足聽之言，乃是自然之至言也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 34
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言暴疾美興不長也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "從事，謂舉動，從事於道者也。道以無形無為成濟萬物，故從事於道者，以無為為君，不言為教，緜緜若存而物得其真，與道同體，故曰同於道。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "得，少也，少則得，故曰得也。行得則與得同體，故曰，同於得也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "失，累多也，累多則失，故曰失也。行失則與失同體，故曰，同於失也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 33
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言隨行其所，故同而應之。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "忠信不足於下，焉有不信焉。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
